PART A — TERMS OF USE
1. About Family CareCircle
Family CareCircle (“Platform”, “we”, “us”) is a family owned digital coordination platform designed to assist individuals and families to organise, store, and share care related information with people they choose, including family members, carers, support workers, and allied health practitioners.
Family CareCircle is a technology platform only. It does not provide healthcare, medical, clinical, therapeutic, legal, or professional services and is not an NDIS provider.
________________________________________
2. Account Roles Overview
Each Family CareCircle account has defined roles to support safe coordination of care and clear responsibility.
These roles are:
•	Owner
•	Administrator
•	User
Everyone is invited to the platform as Guests, with and assigned a role. Each role has different permissions and responsibilities, described below.
________________________________________
3. Owner
The Owner is the individual who:
•	Creates the Family CareCircle account, or
•	Is designated as the account owner
The Owner:
•	Holds global administrative control over the Family CareCircle
•	Manages subscription and billing (where applicable)
•	May assign or remove Administrator access
•	May downgrade or remove Administrator permissions, including their own
•	Retains ultimate control of the account lifecycle
The Owner may also act as an Administrator but is the only role with responsibility for payment and subscription management.
________________________________________
4. Administrator
An Administrator is a user with elevated permissions assigned by the Owner.
The Administrator:
•	Manages day to day use of the Family CareCircle
•	Invites and removes Guests
•	Assigns and changes Guest access levels
•	Controls what information is shared
•	Responds to requests for access, correction, or deletion of information within the Family CareCircle
An Administrator may manage care for themselves, a child, or another family member and confirms they have authority to do so.
Administrators do not control subscription payments unless they are also the Owner.
________________________________________
5. Guests
All individuals invited to a Family CareCircle who are not the Owner or an Administrator are considered Guests.
Guests may include family members, informal carers, support workers, allied health practitioners, or other persons authorised by the Administrator.
Guests access the Platform only at the direction and permission of the Owner or Administrator.
________________________________________
6. Guest Access Levels
Family CareCircle uses role based access controls as a risk management measure to reduce unauthorised modification of sensitive information.
All Guests are assigned one of the following access levels by an Administrator or the Owner:
User (Default)
•	View and create access only
•	Cannot modify, or delete information
•	Must request changes via the Administrator or platform support
Editor
•	May create, modify, and delete their own contributions
•	Cannot modify or delete information entered by others
•	Remains responsible for the accuracy and appropriateness of content they contribute
Admin (Guest Admin)
•	May be granted delegated administrative permissions
•	Acts on behalf of the Administrator within the scope assigned
•	Does not become the Owner and does not gain subscription or billing control
Access levels may be changed or revoked at any time by the Owner or an Administrator.
________________________________________
7. Allied Health Practitioners and Service Providers
If you are an allied health practitioner or service provider using Family CareCircle:
•	You confirm you have authority to use the Platform for coordination purposes
•	You acknowledge that Family CareCircle does not replace your organisation’s required clinical or record keeping systems
•	You remain solely responsible for: 
o	Professional conduct
o	Clinical decision making
o	Accuracy of information you contribute
o	Compliance with professional and legal obligations
Use of the Platform does not create any supervisory, employment, or clinical relationship with Family CareCircle.
________________________________________
8. Ownership of Data
•	All data entered into a Family CareCircle is owned by the Owner
•	The Owner authorises Administrators to manage the data on their behalf
•	Family CareCircle does not claim ownership of user generated content
•	Guests contribute information at the invitation and authority of the Owner or Administrator
________________________________________
9. User Responsibility and Risk Acknowledgement
Users acknowledge that:
•	They are responsible for the accuracy of information they contribute
•	The Owner and Administrators control access and sharing
•	Digital platforms carry inherent security risks
•	Role based access restrictions are intentional safeguards
Family CareCircle is not responsible for outcomes arising from:
•	Inaccurate or incomplete information
•	Delays in requested changes
•	Decisions made using information stored on the Platform
