PART B — PRIVACY POLICY
14. Our Commitment to Privacy
Family CareCircle is committed to protecting personal and sensitive information in accordance with the Privacy Act 1988 (Cth) and the Australian Privacy Principles (APPs).
We recognise that the Platform may store sensitive health information and take reasonable steps to protect it.
________________________________________
15. Information We Collect
We may collect:
•	Account information (name, email)
•	Care related information entered by users
•	Health information voluntarily uploaded
•	Limited technical and usage data for security and performance
________________________________________
16. Sensitive Information
Sensitive information, including health data:
•	Is collected only with consent
•	Is entered voluntarily by users
•	Is controlled by the Owner and managed by Administrators
We do not use sensitive information for advertising or unrelated purposes.
________________________________________
17. Purpose of Collection
Information is collected to:
•	Enable care coordination
•	Support controlled sharing
•	Maintain platform security
•	Improve functionality
________________________________________
18. Disclosure of Information
Information may be disclosed:
•	To Guests authorised by the Owner or Administrator
•	To trusted service providers required to operate the Platform
•	Where required by law
We do not sell personal information.
________________________________________
19. Data Security
We take reasonable steps to protect information from unauthorised access, misuse, or loss. No digital system is completely risk free.
________________________________________
20. Access and Correction of Information
Family CareCircle supports rights to access and correct personal information under the Privacy Act 1988.
Each Family CareCircle is controlled by its Owner, who authorises Administrators to manage information on their behalf.
Role Based Management
•	The Owner retains ultimate authority over access and correction.
•	Guests with Administrator access are responsible for responding to access, correction, or deletion requests relating to information stored within the Family CareCircle.
•	Guests with Editor access may create, modify, or delete information they personally contributed.
•	Guests with User access have read and write only access and must request changes via an Administrator or platform support.
Family CareCircle does not independently review, modify, or release information without the direction of the Owner or an Administrator, unless required by law.
External Records
Guests who are allied health practitioners remain responsible for records maintained outside the Platform in accordance with their professional obligations.
________________________________________
21. Children and Dependents
Owners and Administrators managing care for a child or dependent confirm they have legal authority to provide consent and manage information.
